• Proof approved, proceed with order._x000D_
• Proof NOT approved and list necessary changes to be made._x000D_

Good morning  Joree and Laura,_x000D_
I hope you are off to a great start to your week !  I know that you are most likely caught up in a whirlwind after being out for the show, but I just wanted to Thank you for spending time with Ann Marie and Katie at the EME Utah  event._x000D_
My name is Michelle Finnigan  and I am your dedicated inside sales rep at AAkron Line . I would be happy to help you with questions on Special pricing, custom or large quantity orders or even ideas to spark your clients interest like virtuals  or sales flyers . The South East Regional Sales Manager Mike Zingale  and  I work closely together , Our contact information is attached and we hope that you will feel free to reach out If you should need any assistance ._x000D_
One of the many benefits of attending the EME meeting is that AAkron Line  would like to extend our EQP program which is good through 12/31/15.  We do require an annual sales volume of $10,000.00 to have the program automatically renewed the following year . Please review the attached artwork carefully. When this copy is approved you are approving both the spelling and overall layout of the ad copy. In your reply please be sure to include one or more of the following statements:_x000D_
      • Proof approved, proceed with order._x000D_
      • Proof NOT approved and list necessary changes to be made._x000D_
      • Advise whether a second proof is required._x000D_
Please note, if the proof has been sent in color, there is no guarantee that the colors you see on your computer screen will be an exact match to the ink or foil colors when the product has been printed. Estimated production time is 7-10 days, after approval on one color imprint orders._x000D_
On Full Color Digital orders, PMS matches are not possible, imprinting method is CMYK format. You will see truest color representation when printed on a white product. Be advised that colors may vary on colored backgrounds. Estimated production time is 10-14 days, after approval on FCD color imprint orders._x000D_
If this proof is not approved within 24 hours, additional time will be necessary_x000D_
If you have any trouble accessing this file or have questions, please do not hesitate to contact me. We thank you for your quick response._x000D_
Please visit us online at, www.aakronline.com<http://www.aakronline.com/> , for "real-time" order tracking!_x000D_

_x000D_
Attached are the program details & requirements for your records. The annual sales volume requirements for this program are $10,000. AAkron is also trailblazing new printing techniques with the introduction of our Full Color Direct printing.  FCD Direct printing offers full color decorating on a growing list of drinkware items on either 1/side, 2/side or a full wrap full color printing for about the same price as 1/c imprinting and for the same set up charge.  Let us show you how you can capitalize on this growing trend so you can part of the FCD printing sales train._x000D_
_x000D_

Good Morning Brittany ~ 2017 will be a special year for the AAkron family; AAkron Line is turning 50 years old.  We have come a long way from the two-car garage that was our first production and office space.   We would not have grown to the company we are today without the support of our customers like you._x000D_
_x000D_
AAkron Line is pleased to announce that National Bank Products has qualified for our 2017 EQP Pricing Program.    This program recognizes and rewards our top clients for their continued partnership and support._x000D_
_x000D_
Attached are the program details & requirements for your records. The annual sales volume requirements for this program are $10,000.   To help ensure that we exceed this requirement for 2017, we can help with marketing support, program suggestions and much more.  Just let us know how we can help._x000D_
_x000D_
New for 2017, we added over 50 new products and we expanded the AAkron exclusive items to over 125 items.  AAkron is also trailblazing new printing techniques with the introduction of our Full Color Direct printing.  FCD Direct printing offers full color decorating on a growing list of drinkware items on either 1/side, 2/side or a full wrap full color printing for about the same price as 1/c imprinting and for the same set up charge.  Let us show you how you can capitalize on this growing trend so you can part of the FCD printing sales train._x000D_
_x000D_
Thank you for the support over the years and we look forward to the next 50 years.   We look forward to making 2017 a success for all,  and further developing our partnership._x000D_

   Hi Tony,_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
   We could use your help! We are just about at our wit’s end with Aakron’s art department in regards to the full color bookmarks we have been ordering. The first time we ever sent the art (earlier this year), we used the dimensions listed on the website. They came back to us and said our dimensions were incorrect. We requested a template for the product, which we received and used to resubmit the art. After that, whenever we have had an order, we have used that same template. On EVERY SINGLE order we have placed, we have gotten calls from Miranda saying the art is not the correct size._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
   Because the front side of the bookmark looks the same on most of our orders, Miranda wants to set it up as stock art and use it as a reorder; however, there is a subtle change in that art on some of the orders. A national hotline number that has been integrated into the art is sometimes changed to a client’s local number. Because the art varies on both the front and back, even when it looks similar, I prefer to send new art each time to make sure we don’t mess up on a reorder._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
   Yesterday, we received yet another call about these bookmarks. Amanda, my art assistant, asked Miranda to send us the template she would prefer us to use. She received back the EXACT template that we received before. When she pointed this out, Miranda then sent the “correct” specs, which differ by only a few hundredths to even a few thousandths of an inch, and apparently are only “approximate!” (I included their email exchange below)._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
   We don’t have any problems with Aakron’s art department on any other product, so it’s baffling to me that this one item can be such a hassle. Because it is happening on every order we place, and this has become a popular product for us, we are seriously considering choosing another vendor to do our bookmark orders. The amount of time wasted going back and forth with Aakron every time we order is ridiculous. Do you have any ideas of how this can be remedied?_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
   Thanks for your help, Tony!_x000D_

Complete the columns we had hidden for the initial Submission  (Columns AE - AU).  Please read the instructions in row 5 carefully on the spreadsheet to complete it as we want the information sent to us.
